♪ ♪

18:08.709 --> 18:10.709
I gave you a lot of money.

18:11.000 --> 18:13.083
I quite might like some more.

18:13.166 --> 18:14.250
I'm-I'm-I'm sorry.

18:14.333 --> 18:16.375
-I don't want sorry.
-Scooter: Dad!

18:16.458 --> 18:17.875
Ruby:
Well, I'm-I'm not having a...

18:18.458 --> 18:19.458
Is that Scooter?

18:19.542 --> 18:20.792
(sigh) No.

18:20.875 --> 18:23.291
-Ruby: Put him on. Hey!
-Hang on.

18:23.375 --> 18:25.583
-Put him on! Hey! Put him--
-Scooter (on phone): Hello.

18:25.667 --> 18:27.625
Scooter! Hey, how are you?

18:27.709 --> 18:29.291
I fell off a trampoline.

18:29.375 --> 18:31.125
Ruby:
Uh, what trampoline?

18:31.208 --> 18:32.291
In a trampoline park.

18:32.375 --> 18:35.083
-Did-did Dad take you--
-No, Sarah took us.

18:36.542 --> 18:38.500
What-- who's Sarah?

18:38.583 --> 18:40.083
Our new au pair.

18:40.166 --> 18:42.375
(stammering)
Uh, your dad got--

18:42.458 --> 18:45.250
Wait, um, is she--
(sigh) Who is she?

18:45.333 --> 18:47.750
-Scooter: She has blue hair.
-Sarah (on phone): Scooter!

18:47.834 --> 18:50.166
-Sarah: We're going!
-And she's taking us for
ice cream, so I better...

18:50.250 --> 18:52.917
I miss you so much.
I'm gonna come home
from my vacation...

18:53.000 --> 18:55.041
-...right now.
-Okay, bye.

18:56.125 --> 18:59.250
-Scooter? Scooter?
-(line disconnects)

19:01.917 --> 19:05.667
♪ There are miles ♪

19:05.750 --> 19:07.500
♪ Between us ♪

19:07.583 --> 19:08.875
(rumbling)

19:08.959 --> 19:13.250
♪ Time between us ♪

19:13.333 --> 19:17.041
♪ There is something
between us ♪

19:19.875 --> 19:20.917
(Ruby sighs)

19:21.000 --> 19:25.333
♪ I may be a fool ♪

19:25.417 --> 19:29.500
♪ To dream of you ♪

19:30.208 --> 19:31.417
(knocking)

19:31.500 --> 19:34.125
♪ But, God, it feels
so good to dream ♪

19:39.625 --> 19:41.750
-Hi!
-Did you get
to speak to him?

19:41.834 --> 19:43.709
Yeah, Scooter,
just-just a broken arm.

19:43.792 --> 19:45.667
Well, where was
Laurence at the time?

19:45.750 --> 19:49.375
Oh, well, we-we-we can't
watch them every second.

19:49.458 --> 19:51.709
-He got a nanny.
-Of course he did.

19:51.792 --> 19:53.709
And Scooter
wasn't even missing me.

19:53.792 --> 19:54.875
Am I--
am I just the lady

19:54.959 --> 19:57.625
who-who washes
his emoji pajamas?

19:57.709 --> 19:59.000
-Ruby...
-What?

19:59.083 --> 20:00.375
Well first,
you complain

20:00.458 --> 20:01.792
that Laurence is calling you
over 100 times and now

20:01.875 --> 20:03.375
you're freaking out that
nobody wants you enough!

20:03.458 --> 20:04.875
-No, but what--
-Look.

20:04.959 --> 20:06.709
You made
a decision, okay?

20:06.792 --> 20:08.208
The kids will survive.

20:08.291 --> 20:09.875
They'll be happy to see you
when they see you,

20:09.959 --> 20:11.834
and when you've gone,
well, they'll get on fine.

20:12.166 --> 20:14.709
I don't want them
to get on without me.

20:14.792 --> 20:16.291
-You don't?
-No!

20:17.000 --> 20:19.667
Well, go back home then.

20:21.000 --> 20:22.583
I can't do that to Billy.

20:22.667 --> 20:24.291
-No?
-No, he needs me.

20:24.375 --> 20:26.166
You don't know him anymore.

20:28.083 --> 20:31.000
Me and Billy have been
working together for years.

20:31.083 --> 20:33.875
♪ ♪

20:33.959 --> 20:35.333
Oh...

20:35.417 --> 20:37.959
You're just so gullible, Ruby.

20:38.333 --> 20:40.250
(whispers):
Get outta my roomette.

20:40.333 --> 20:41.792
I just need you
to do one thing.

20:41.875 --> 20:43.417
-What?
-Gimme the money.

20:43.500 --> 20:45.583
-Hm?
-The bag of money.

20:45.667 --> 20:46.959
I don't understand.

20:47.041 --> 20:49.041
What I'm saying is that
I would like you to give me

20:49.125 --> 20:50.917
that bag of cash
so that I won't

20:51.000 --> 20:53.208
have to ruin your
life because...

20:53.709 --> 20:55.125
(Ruby and Billy
moaning over phone)

20:55.208 --> 20:57.333
Oh! Oh! Sh--

20:57.417 --> 20:59.417
I was in your hotel
last night,

20:59.500 --> 21:02.208
and now that I've got
Laurence's number...

21:04.667 --> 21:06.208
You were my friend!

21:06.291 --> 21:08.458
Well, I didn't
expect to like you.

21:08.542 --> 21:09.709
The money.

21:17.208 --> 21:19.250
♪

21:21.500 --> 21:22.875
(unzips bag)

21:24.458 --> 21:27.125
Billy won't ever be
entirely honest with you.

21:27.208 --> 21:28.875
Remember that.

21:36.709 --> 21:39.250
(indistinct chatter)

21:49.834 --> 21:51.792
-Billy: There you are.
-Okay, so--

21:51.875 --> 21:53.834
-Listen--
-I was wrong about Alice.

21:53.917 --> 21:56.166
-Listen, Ruby, I need
to tell you something.
-No, listen--

21:56.250 --> 21:59.166
I can't do any more
secret-keeping from you.
Fiona, Alice,

21:59.250 --> 22:00.834
whatever she's
calling herself,

22:00.917 --> 22:04.041
she isn't following you,
okay? She's following me.

22:04.125 --> 22:06.083
Oh, I know.
(clears throat)

22:08.750 --> 22:10.083
Oh.

22:10.875 --> 22:12.667
She used to work for me

22:12.750 --> 22:14.875
and she's furious at me
for ending the tour.

22:14.959 --> 22:17.709
She was always very
dedicated to her job,
and now she's angry

22:17.792 --> 22:20.041
-'cause she thinks she
won't get anything else.
-Okay.

22:20.125 --> 22:22.083
(grunts) Is that all?

22:22.625 --> 22:23.834
Yeah.

22:28.458 --> 22:29.500
No.

22:30.834 --> 22:32.625
I... I wasn't

22:32.709 --> 22:36.750
totally honest with you
about what happened on stage.

22:38.417 --> 22:40.000
I, um...

22:40.750 --> 22:43.417
Before I walked off,
I told everyone,

22:43.500 --> 22:46.083
including Jackie
and her dead husband,

22:46.166 --> 22:48.792
that they were
a bunch of cunts.

22:49.667 --> 22:52.375
And the crowd sort of
turned on me,

22:52.458 --> 22:55.000
and now there's all
these online opinions

22:55.083 --> 22:57.625
going around that
I'm a bit of-of a murderer.

23:03.166 --> 23:04.959
I gave Alice the money.

23:07.291 --> 23:09.333
-Oh, God!
-But it's okay!

23:09.417 --> 23:11.291
-Oh, God! Fucking no!
-No, Billy!

23:11.375 --> 23:14.083
Billy! Listen to me!
I've got you now,

23:14.166 --> 23:15.792
and we're not gonna let
her get away with this.

23:15.875 --> 23:17.250
For God's sake.

23:17.333 --> 23:20.542
We're on a train.
She literally
can't have gone far.

23:21.583 --> 23:23.625
♪ ♪

23:23.709 --> 23:25.458
-Can you see her?
-No.

23:25.542 --> 23:27.166
(door hissing)

23:30.959 --> 23:32.875
-Billy: Is that her?
-Ruby: Where?

23:32.959 --> 23:34.125
Billy: There.

23:34.208 --> 23:36.458
-Ruby: Maybe.
-Billy: Okay. Go.

23:38.333 --> 23:39.709
No.

23:39.792 --> 23:40.959
Hey, have you seen a--

23:41.041 --> 23:42.208
Your other girlfriend?

23:42.291 --> 23:44.041
She went that way.

23:45.208 --> 23:47.000
(doors hissing)

23:50.917 --> 23:53.041
(doors hissing)

23:56.333 --> 23:57.417
(door opens)

23:58.083 --> 23:59.208
Ugh!

24:07.000 --> 24:08.166
Billy:
Fuck.

24:08.250 --> 24:09.583
There she is.

24:09.667 --> 24:11.375
-Billy: Go.
-Ruby: Go, go!

24:12.208 --> 24:14.667
♪ ♪

24:16.542 --> 24:17.792
Billy: Fuck!

24:17.875 --> 24:20.166
♪

24:22.959 --> 24:24.625
-(grunts)
-Man: Shit!

24:24.709 --> 24:26.291
Ruby: Sorry, sorry!

24:26.375 --> 24:28.375
Oh, we're going to hell.

24:28.458 --> 24:30.583
♪

24:39.625 --> 24:40.917
-Billy: Hang on!
-Ruby: No!

24:41.250 --> 24:43.041
Come on! Come on!

24:45.333 --> 24:47.208
-Fiona! Can we go back...
-I know you're angry with me...

24:47.291 --> 24:49.500
-to just being normal friends?
-but I need that money back!

24:49.583 --> 24:50.917
Fuck you!

24:51.750 --> 24:53.458
Ruby: No! Oh!

24:55.166 --> 24:56.875
Where the fuck did she go?

25:00.000 --> 25:03.125
♪ ♪

25:22.542 --> 25:25.625
♪ ♪

25:52.583 --> 25:55.667
♪ ♪

26:22.583 --> 26:25.667
♪ ♪

26:41.041 --> 26:42.542
♪ (UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYS) ♪

26:42.625 --> 26:44.291
RUBY RICHARDSON:
We're coming to get you!

26:44.375 --> 26:45.792
-(GROANS)
-RUBY: Have you slept with her?

26:45.875 --> 26:48.166
What sort of a question is that?
Of course I have.

26:48.375 --> 26:49.959
We were working together
for seven years.

26:50.041 --> 26:51.291
It would have been rude not to.

26:51.875 --> 26:53.125
♪ (UPBEAT MUSIC CONTINUES) ♪

26:53.375 --> 26:55.083
Do you get the feeling
like we're walking away

26:55.166 --> 26:57.041
-from something...
-(DOOR CREAKS)

26:57.959 --> 26:59.041
Hello?

26:59.875 --> 27:01.542
...that we can never walk away
from?

27:02.500 --> 27:04.458
RUBY: I need you
to go with me now.

27:05.083 --> 27:08.750
Hi, ma'am, could you take us
to the nearest station?

27:10.667 --> 27:11.625
Hello.

27:12.250 --> 27:14.083
♪ (MUSIC CONCLUDES) ♪
